### Authentication Endpoints
### Base URL: http://localhost:8000

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@apiVersion = v1
@username = testuser
@email = test@example.com
@password = testpassword123

### 1. Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###

### 2. User Registration
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "tuanhanb98",
    "email": "tuanhanb98@gmail.com",
    "password": "12345678",
    "full_name": "Manh Tuan Ha"
}

###

### 3. User Login (OAuth2 Token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/auth/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username={{username}}&password={{password}}

###

### 4. Get Current User Profile (Protected)
# Copy the access_token from the login response above
@accessToken = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJ0ZXN0dXNlciIsImV4cCI6MTc2MTgxMDIxOH0.JMoW0UrtMqas_x8xnJ4jbNq8NWFxsoWhWb8rcXq0iYs

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/auth/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### 5. Test Invalid Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/{{apiVersion}}/auth/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=invalid@example.com&password=wrongpassword

###

